org.jpc.engine.prolog

Interface PrologEngine

  • All Superinterfaces:
    PrologDatabase
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPrologEngine, JpcEngine, LogtalkEngine, PrologEngineProxy

    public interface PrologEngine
extends PrologDatabase
    An abstract interface for a Prolog engine session. Depending on the underlying driver library, multiple sessions can be spawned in the JVM (e.g., InterProlog), or only one (e.g., JPL).
    Author:
    sergioc

      • close

        void close()
        Close the logic engine and free associated resources. Once the session is not required it can be closed. However, some drivers do not allow this and will throw an UnsupportedOperationException instead

      • isCloseable

        boolean isCloseable()
        Returns:
        true if the Prolog engine can be closed (i.e., its resources can be freed). false otherwise.

      • isMultiThreaded

        boolean isMultiThreaded()
        Returns:
        true if the Prolog engine can manage concurrent requests (e.g., multiple queries open at the same time). false otherwise.
